messages.message:
Quick Cypress status:
• upstream-integrations is failing because of our outlook mailbox subscription expired, working on getting this fixed
• advanced-apps was failing because a component was remounting, I have a fix coming for this (but there's another bug, see below that will also prevent it from succeeding)
• @Victor Zeng payment is failing (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/16797/overview/dcea53e7-7f1e-4501-b98c-da46303100bd/replay?att=1&roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1) for migrated user test with the error `Error: no auth mechanism defined`
• Several extraction tests are failing with extraction errors: `"msg": "Error during refiner extraction: model result is empty due to an error in model service\n\n METADATA:\n\n\n{\"extraction_result\": null}"`. Backend issue maybe? @Serena @danny.lan. Affected tests are aihub-custom-function-field, aihub-data-types, aihub-derived-field, aihub-extraction, aihub-quick-clean-refinement, aihub-redigitization, aihub-refinement, aihub-split-by-page, aihub-split-classification, build-billing (so like all the build ones)
• I see one for aihub-templates that failed on the first try then didn't clean up correctly so failed on the next two tries - I'll look into fixing that @Serena 
• Digitization is failing in converse-app, I believe it's the same issue as for build (it says "failed to create index")
• Looking into a new downstream-integrations failure for custom functions
• search-app is failing but it looks like it's been failing for a really long time. @Subash do you want to just skip this test if it's not in use?
• run-app, run-public-app, review-manager-dashboard, review-reviewer-dashboard are failing because the actual runs are failing - I'm wondering if this is related to the build errors but I can look into this a little deeper to double check @Serena 
• documents-grid, advanced-apps, field-editor, file-list, nested-field-editor, and results-table are all failing because files aren't uploading to be able to run them, probably the same indexing error
Sounds like all the model related ones are a known issue related to the langchain upgrade

> Sounds like all the model related ones are a known issue related to the langchain upgrade
is there another thread where you already see this being discussed?
btw thanks for looking into `aihub-templates` ! it seems that the second `it` block actually depends on the first `it` block and can’t be run independently

btw i took a quick peek at why `run-app` failed, and it’s running into a protobuf error when running the classification step

i assume run-public-app, review-manager-dashboard, review-reviewer-dashboard are also failing for the same reason (i haven’t verified yet though)

this protobuf error should be fixed by https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/67076, which has already been merged

so :crossed_fingers: that a lot of these failures will disappear after the next aihub-sandbox deployment!
Yay! I'll do another pass tomorrow after this fix and the langchain fix (whatever it is) have been deployed
yeah i’m not sure if there are more langchain fixes pending besides the one i linked above :disappointed:
